# Documentation And Canvas Sync

When a change is large enough to affect repository documentation, update all relevant documentation surfaces in the same change:

- Update the repo docs that own the topic, especially `docs/repo-maintenance.md` and `docs/repo-architecture-graph.md` for architecture, ownership, data flow, generated artifacts, SEO, worker endpoints, deployment, or environment changes.
- Update `docs/personal-portfolio-repo-docs.canvas.tsx` so the repo-published canvas source stays aligned with the current architecture and known drift.
- If the live Cursor canvas exists, mirror the same meaningful updates into `/Users/hassanraza/.cursor/projects/Users-hassanraza-Projects-Personal-Portfolio/canvases/personal-portfolio-repo-docs.canvas.tsx`.
- Keep the Known Drift / Follow-ups section current: remove resolved drift and add newly discovered drift.

Do not leave the markdown docs and canvas docs disagreeing about routes, content models, generation paths, worker contracts, deployment flow, or validation commands.
